## 7. SRS v1.2 reconciliations (defects to fix in the spec)

- **Air-gap vs Hybrid (resolved → LAN-only).** Update SI-6/DC-4/SE-4 to "no internet egress; LAN-restricted to Ollama host + front-end RPC." Escalation = local model tier swap, not cloud.
- **"Output ONLY code, no explanations" (Appendix B) vs accessibility.** The persona filter governs **LLM task output** (suppress hedging/refusal). **STATUS_BLOCK, error summaries, and TUI are system-generated by `caaa-core`**, not the model — so they are exempt and reliable. Clarify this boundary in the Constitutional Layer Document.
- **Duplicate ID namespace.** `DC-*` is used for both *Discrepancy Classification* (§3.2.9) and *Design Constraints* (§3.6). Rename §3.6 to `DZ-*` (or `CON-*`) to remove collision.
- **"Single static binary" (DC-3) vs daemon+applet(+optional client).** Becomes **a small set of static binaries** (`caaa-core`, `caaa-applet`, optional `caaa-client`). Note the amendment.
- **Obsidian vault not in SRS v1.2 requirement tables** though present in your brief. Add a `VL-*` requirement group (vault layout, NL note creation, pattern extraction, decision logging, sync, audit-on-write).
- **Embedded vs subprocess for Prolog/Lisp.** Prefer embedded (`scryer-prolog`, `steel`) to preserve near-single-binary + offline; fall back to `swipl`/`sbcl` subprocess only if rule expressiveness requires it.

